By Bashir Rabe Mani The Durbin Katsina, District Head of Mani in Mani Local Government Area (LGA) of Katsina State, Alhaiji Umar Babani, will on Saturday mark his 20-years on the throne. Babani said in a statement issued on Tuesday, in Abuja that the historic event would begin on Thursday with the recitation of the Glorious Qurâ€™an and special prayers. The traditional ruler said that the event would be followed by a novelty football match between youth groups in the area on Thursday, to boost peace and unity. Babani said that seven members of the royal family would on Saturday be turbaned as traditional title holders. He said that the event was aimed at showing gratitude to the Almighty Allah for blessing him with a peaceful and successful reign. Babani, while commending the people of the district for their sustained support, urged them to continue to live in peace and harmony.( NAN)